_30.title: non-closed_areas
_30.description: This way is tagged with ''([\w:]+)=(\w+)''and should be closed-loop

_40.title: dead-ended one-ways
_40.description: The first node \(id (\d+)\) of this one-way is not connected to any other way

_41.description: The last node \(id (\d+)\) of this one-way is not connected to any other way

_42.description: This node cannot be reached because one-ways only lead away from here

_43.description: You cannot escape from this node because one-ways only lead to here

_50.title: almost-junctions
_50.description: This node is very close but not connected to way #(\d+)

_72.description: This node is not member of any way and does not have any tags

_73.description: This way has a tracktype tag but no highway tag

_75.description: This (node|way|relation) has a name \((.+)\) but no other tag

_90.title: motorways without ref
_90.description: This way is tagged as motorway and therefore needs a ref nat_ref or int_ref tag

_100.title: places of worship without religion
_100.description: This (node|way|relation) is tagged as place of worship and therefore needs a religion tag

_110.title: point of interest without name
_110.description: This node is tagged as ([\w:]+) and therefore needs a name tag

_120.title: ways without nodes
_120.description: This way has just one single node

_130.title: floating islands
_130.description: This way is not connected to the rest of the map

_150.title: railway crossing without tag
_150.description: This crossing of a highway and a railway needs to be tagged as railway=crossing or railway=level_crossing

_160.title: wrongly used railway tag
_160.description: There are ways in different layers coming together in this railway crossing. There are ways tagged as tunnel or bridge coming together in this railway crossing

_180.title: relations without type
_180.description: This relation has no type tag which is mandatory for relations

_190.title: intersections without junctions
_190.description: Finds way crossings on same layer without common node as a junction

_191.title: highway-highway
_191.description: This (highway) intersects the (highway) #(\d+) but there is no junction node

_194.title: waterway-waterway
_194.description: This (waterway) intersects the (waterway) #(\d+) but there is no junction node

_195.title: cycleway-cycleway
_195.description: This (cycleway/footpath) intersects the (cycleway/footpath) #(\d+) but there is no junction node

_196.title: highway-cycleway
_196.description: This (highway|cycleway/footpath) intersects the (highway|cycleway/footpath) #(\d+) but there is no junction node

_200.title: overlapping ways
_200.description: Finds overlapping ways on same layer

_210.title: loopings
_210.description: These errors contain self intersecting ways

_211.description: This way contains more than one node at least twice\. Nodes are ((?:#\d+(?:, )?)+)\. This may or may not be an error

_212.description: This way has only two different nodes and contains one of them more than once

_220.title: misspelled tags
_220.description: This (node|way|relation) is tagged '([\w]+)(:([\w]+))?=(.+)' where "(\2|\3|\4|\5)" looks like "([\w\s]+)"

_221.description: The key of this (node|way|relation)''s tag is ''key'': key=(.+)

_230.title: layer conflicts
_230.description: Connected ways should be on the same layer. Crossings on intermediate nodes of ways on different layers are obviously wrong. Junctions on end-nodes of ways on different layers are also deprecated, but common practice. So you may ignore this part of the check and switch them off separately. Please note that bridges are set to layer +1, and tunnels to -1, anything else to layer 0 implicitly if no layer tag is present.

_231.title: mixed layers intersection
_231.description: This node is a junction of ways on different layers: ((?:#\d+\(-?\d+\),?)+)

_232.title: strange layers
_232.description: This (bridge|tunnel) is tagged with layer (-?\d+)\. This need not be an error but it looks strange

_270.title: motorways connected directly
_270.description: This node is a junction of a motorway and a highway other than motorway, motorway_link, trunk, rest_area or construction. Service or unclassified is only valid if it has access=no/private or it leads to a motorway service area or if it is a service=parking_aisle.

_280.title: boundaries
_280.description: Administrative Boundaries can be expressed either by tagging ways or by adding them to a relation. They should be closed-loop sequences of ways, they must not self-intersect or split and they must have a name and an admin_level.

_282.title: missing admin level
_282.description: The boundary of (.+) has no (?:valid numeric )?admin_level\..*

_283.title: no closed loop
_283.description: The boundary of (.+) is not closed-loop

_285.title: admin_level too high
_285.description: This boundary-way has admin_level (-?\d+) but belongs to a relation with lower admin_level (higher priority); it should have the lowest admin_level of all relations

_290.title: restrictions
_290.description: Analyses all relations tagged type=restriction or following variations type=restriction:hgv type=restriction:caravan type=restriction:motorcar type=restriction:bus type=restriction:agricultural type=restriction:motorcycle type=restriction:bicycle and type=restriction:hazmat

_292.title: missing from way
_292.description: A turn-restriction needs exactly one from member\. This one has (\d+)

_293.title: missing to way
_293.description: A turn-restriction needs exactly one to member\. This one has (\d+)

_294.title: from or to not a way
_294.description: From- and To-members of turn restrictions need to be ways\. ((?:(?:from|to) (?:node|relation) #\d+,?)+)

_295.title: via is not on the way ends
_295.description: via \(node #(\d+)\) is not the first or the last member of from \(way #(\d+)\)

_296.title: wrong restriction angle
_296.description: restriction type is (\w+) but angle is (\d+) degrees. Maybe the restriction type is not appropriate?

_298.title: already restricted by oneway
_298.description: entry already prohibited by oneway tag on (\d+)

_310.title: roundabouts
_310.description: Analyses ways with tag junction=roundabout. More then one way can form a roundabout. It supports tag oneway=-1

_311.title: not closed loop
_311.description: This way is part of a roundabout but is not closed-loop. (split carriageways approaching a roundabout should not be tagged as roundabout)

_312.title: wrong direction
_312.description: If this ((?:mini_)?roundabout) is in a country with (left|right)-hand traffic then its orientation goes the wrong way around

_313.title: faintly connected
_313.description: This roundabout has only (\d) other roads connected. Roundabouts typically have three

_320.title: *_link connections
_320.description: This way is tagged as highway=(\w+)_link but doesn't have a connection to any other \1 or \1_link

_350.title: bridge-tags
_350.description: This bridge does not have a tag in common with its surrounding ways that shows the purpose of this bridge. There should be one of these tags: (.+)
_350.NOTE: Group can be arbitrary list of form: key=value,key=value,key=value...

_370.title: doubled places
_370.description: This node has tags in common with the surrounding way #(\d+) ((?:\(including the name '.+'\) )?)and seems to be redundand

_380.title: non-physical use of sport-tag
_380.description: This way is tagged sport=(\w+) but has no physical tag like e.g. leisure, building, amenity or highway

_401.title: missing turn restriction
_401.description: ways (\d+) and (\d+) join in a very sharp angle here and there is no oneway tag or turn restriction that prevents turning( from way (\1|\2) to (\1|\2))?

_402.title: impossible angles
_402.description: this way bends in a very sharp angle here

_410.title: website
_410.description: Web pages are analyzed. Web page is defined by any of the following tags website=* url=* website:mobile=* contact:website=* contact:url=* image=* source:website=* or source:url=*

_411.title: http error
_411.description: The URL \(\1\) cannot be opened \(HTTP status code (\d+)\)

_412.title: domain hijacking
_412.description: Possible domain squatting: \1\. Suspicious text is: ''(.+)''

_413.title: non-match
_413.description: Content of the URL (\1) did not contain these keywords: \((.+)\)

_20.title: multiple nodes on the same spot
_20.description: There is more than one node in this spot\. Offending node IDs: ((?:#\d+,?)+)

_60.title: depreciated tags
_60.description: This (node|way|relation) uses deprecated tag '([\w:]+)=(.+)'\. Please use "(.+)" instead!

_360.title: language unknown
_360.description: It would be nice if this (node|way|relation) had an additional tag 'name:XX=(.+)' where XX shows the language of its name '\2'

_390.title: missing tracktype
_390.description: This track doesn''t have a tracktype
